ngegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22661.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Caster robes</span><hr size=1> As a necromancer I am interested in int, mana, HP, resists, AC, stamina (for more hp's) and of course free spelleffects. Mix all these together and you can get alot of combinations making alot of different gear possible.<br><br>Sure, gear is more important for meeles than for casters but I am still quite crippled if I don't have my gear since 40% of my mana and Hp's comes from it, not to mention resists.<br><br>Caster loot is much more rare than melee loot. No it is not fair. A caster likes a new toy just as much as the next fellow.<br><br>Sarastro D'rknes, 59'th Necromancer<br>Oody, 47'th Rogue <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uultravoices.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ultravoices</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 8:45:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22661.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Caster robes</span><hr size=1> <i>Certain spells from an enc may be resisted because of the lack of cha,</i><br><br>Once you are of A Certain Level, lack of CHA has very little to do with it. <br>It is about the lack of HP.<br><br>nekkid, and unbuffed, I have about 875hp and 312AC<br><br>With gear, and ubuffed, I have about 1400hp and 600AC<br><br>Doesn't seem like a lot, but that extra HP from gear gives me one more attempt at mezzing, one more resist, the time to mez one extra mob before falling into frenzy HP range or outright death, a little more time for a healer to land a heal.<br><br>As for robes? I have several, which have slightly different yet un